description: A hollow book has the covers and spine of a normal tome and blends in with other books on a shelf. Its pages, however, are glued together and their middles cut out (usually leaving a half-inch border of paper) to form a space.
An empty, hard bound journal containing 25 pages.
Essential for wizards, a spellbook is a leather-bound tome with 100 blank vellum pages suitable for recording spells.
